<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pericyclocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pericyclocera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4093" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericyclocera</taxonomicName>
Schmitz, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Paraphiochaeta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paraphiochaeta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4093" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paraphiochaeta</taxonomicName>
Malloch, and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Plastophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plastophora" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4093" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Plastophora</taxonomicName>
Brues. The species herein described is easily distinguished from species once classified in these genera by presence of the wing spot.
</paragraph>
